    <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
      <head>Biographical History</head>
      <p>Charles Van Devander  was an American journalist.  He was a Washington 
		correspondent for the <emph render="italic">New York Post</emph>, author of 
		<emph render="italic">The Big Bosses</emph> (1944) on corruption in government, 
		and served as Press Secretary and Executive Assistant to New York Governor Averell Harriman.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
      <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
      <p>The <emph render="bold">Charles Van Devander Papers</emph> consist of 
		correspondence, news releases, and typescripts.  
		<emph render="bold">Correspondence</emph> is with New York State government officials and departments, including Senator Daniel Patrick Moynihan and Governor Averell Harriman.  
		<emph render="bold">News releases</emph> cover July 1956 to Jun 1957.  
		<emph render="bold">Typescript</emph> contains a few fragments of 
		typewritten material.</p>
    </scopecontent>
    <arrangement encodinganalog="351$a">
      <head>Arrangement of the Collection</head>
      <p>All series are arranged chronologically.</p>
    </arrangement>
